Description
----------
The QMDB _init_dir function unconditionally deletes the entire data directory
and recreates it from scratch every time init_dir is called. This means that
reopening a QMDB database wipes all previously persisted state.

The fix makes _init_dir idempotent: if the top-level directory already exists,
we assume the database was previously initialized and return early. Fresh
initialization (creating the dir, shard files, twig files, and MetaDB) only
runs when the directory does not yet exist.

Upstream impact: This should be submitted as a PR to the qmdb repository.

Workaround in btc-rust
-----------------------
In crates/storage/src/qmdb_backend.rs, QmdbDatabase::new() already guards the
init_dir call behind a check:

    let data_subdir = std::path::Path::new(dir).join("data");
    if !data_subdir.exists() {
        AdsCore::init_dir(&config);
    }

This workaround prevents the destructive init_dir from being called when data
already exists, so the node survives restarts even with the unpatched upstream.
